<div>
    Correct OEE = (Availability) x (Performance) x (Quality)
    Run Time vs Scheduled Time         % of Maximum Speed                   % Good Parts
    75%           x            85%         x      97%     =   62% OEE
</div>
<br />
<div>
    Simple   OEE = (Good Quantity Produced) / (Maximum Possible Production)
    Sum of good quality products produced in shift                    Maximum rate per hour  x  Number of  Hours in Shift
    4,960 units         /       8,000       =   62% OEE
</div>


